Field3D
------------------------------------------
Field3D is an open source library for storing voxel data. It provides C++
classes that handle in-memory storage and a file format based on HDF5 that
allows the C++ objects to be written to and read from disk.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libboost_program_options1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_regex1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_system1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_thread1.66-1.66.0-1
  libField3D-devel-1.7.2-1bl4
  libField3D1.7-1.7.2-1bl4
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libhdf5_103-1.10.6-1
  libilmbase12-2.2.0-1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1
  zlib0-1.2.11-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://sites.google.com/site/field3d/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/imageworks/Field3D/archive/v1.7.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack Field3D-1.7.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./Field3D-1.7.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/Field3D-1.7.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/Field3D-1.7.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libField3D1.7-1.7.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libField3D-devel-1.7.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

